<h3>How to prepare your JDK to use OC Volume?</h3>
<ol>
<li>Find your JDK installation directory. For example: c:\jdk1.3
<li>Go to JRE's Extension directory. For example: c:\jdk1.3\jre\lib\ext
<li>Copy ocvolume.jar to JRE's Extension directory
<li>Done! You can now import the ocvolume package to your classes and it
</ol>
<h2>Sample programs</h2>
The sample programs are intended to show you how to use OC Volume recognition engine.
